# W5-a HONEST REJECTION: a `str` method called on `bytes` (`b.upper()`) is an
# honest "type `bytes` has no method" CHECK error, not a stub and not a rustc
# E0599 leak. The whole bytes method surface (hex/decode/find/split/...) is the
# W5-b wave; until then every `b.method()` is an honest unknown-method error.
